The Vice President, Joe Biden, released a statement on the passing of Sargent Shriver. He praised Shriver for his dedication to serving others and highlighted his achievements, such as founding the Peace Corps, leading the war on poverty, and advocating for people with intellectual disabilities. The Vice President also mentioned Shriver's personal impact on his own life, as Shriver helped him during his Senate campaign in 1972. The statement concluded with condolences to Shriver's family and a celebration of his long and impactful life.